## Jenkins Pipeline Best Practices on Kubernetes## 
1.1. Multibranch Pipeline Best Practices## 

1.1.1. Jenkinsfile Design

pipeline {
    agent {
        kubernetes {
            yaml '''
            apiVersion: v1
            kind: Pod
            spec:
                containers:
                - name: build
                  image: maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17
                  resources:
                      requests:
                          cpu: "500m"
                          memory: "512Mi"
                      limits:
                          cpu: "2"
                          memory: "2Gi"
            '''
            podRetention(never())
            activeDeadlineSeconds(1800)
            idleMinutes(0)
        }
    }
    options {
        timeout(time: 30, unit: 'MINUTES')
        disableConcurrentBuilds()
        buildDiscarder(logRotator(numToKeepStr: '10'))
        skipDefaultCheckout(true)
    }
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                checkout([
                    $class: 'GitSCM',
                    branches: scm.branches,
                    extensions: [
                        [$class: 'CloneOption', depth: 1, shallow: true, noTags: true, timeout: 10],
                        [$class: 'CleanBeforeCheckout']
                    ],
                    userRemoteConfigs: scm.userRemoteConfigs
                ])
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                container('build') {
                    sh 'mvn clean install'
                }
            }
        }
        stage('Tests') {
            parallel {
                stage('Unit') { 
                    steps { container('build') { sh 'make unit-test' } } 
                }
                stage('Integration') { 
                    steps { container('build') { sh 'make int-test' } } 
                }
            }
        }
    }
    post {
        always { junit '*/target/surefire-reports/*.xml' }
        success { slackSend channel: '#ci', message: "✅ ${env.JOB_NAME} passed" }
        failure { slackSend channel: '#ci', message: "❌ ${env.JOB_NAME} failed" }
    }
}

## 1.1.2. Branch Management

* Limit branch discovery: Only build branches matching patterns (e.g., main, dev, feature/, PR-) to avoid wasting resources.
* Branch strategy: Auto-delete jobs for branches that no longer exist on the remote repository.
* Use build Discarder: Keep only N recent builds per branch to save cluster master storage.
* Disable concurrent builds: Prevent the same branch from running in parallel unless explicitly intended.

## 1.1.3. Multibranch Configuration

* ✅ Scan interval: Do not scan too frequently. Use webhooks instead.
* ✅ Webhooks over polling: Configure GitHub or GitLab webhooks to trigger builds instantly.
* ✅ Branch source traits: Filter systematically by name, pull request trust level, and discovery behaviours.

