## 1.2. Shallow Clone (Reduce Git Overhead)
Full git history is almost never needed for CI builds. Use shallow clone to save time, network bandwidth, and disk space.

checkout([
    $class: 'GitSCM',
    branches: scm.branches,
    extensions: [
        [$class: 'CloneOption', depth: 1, shallow: true, noTags: true, timeout: 10],
        [$class: 'CleanBeforeCheckout']
    ],
    userRemoteConfigs: scm.userRemoteConfigs
])


* depth: 1: Only fetch the latest commit instead of the full git history.
* shallow: true: Enable shallow clone functionality.
* noTags: true: Skip fetching tags to reduce metadata processing overhead.
* timeout: 10: Fail fast if the cloning operation takes too long.

