## 1.4. Avoid Unnecessary Resource Usage

* Shallow clone: Avoids cloning gigabytes of historical git repository data.
* Don't install tools at build time: Bake required binaries into custom agent images instead.
* Avoid docker pull of large images every build: Utilize Kaniko step structures with --cache=true flag.
* Don't run idle agent pods: Enforce podRetention(never()) so agent pods terminate instantly post-build.
* Limit workspace size: Clean workspaces and don't archive unnecessary files.
* Multi-stage container builds: Keep final system images small to reduce registry storage costs.
* Prune Jenkins build history: Always use buildDiscarder(logRotator(numToKeepStr: '10')).
* Avoid re-downloading dependencies: Mount a shared PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC) cache for Maven or npm.
* Set timeouts: Kill runaway processes early using timeout(time: 30, unit: 'MINUTES').

## 1.4.1. Agent Pod Anti-Pattern vs Best Practice## ❌ BAD — Installs tools every build
Wastes time, package registry bandwidth, and processing cycles.

container('build') {
    sh '''
    apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq maven
    mvn clean install
    '''
}

## ✅ GOOD — Tools pre-baked in image
Nothing to download at runtime. Ready instantly.

container('build') {
    sh 'mvn clean install'
}

